![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1596582927780-QUDO42M19MFF7Y74TEAG/image-asset.jpeg)

Last year we were BLOWN AWAY by the first season of The Umbrella Academy on Netflix. The sibling rivalry, superpowers, and action-packed episodes made it a front runner for best comic book TV show of 2019. Season 2 dropped this weekend, and boy it did not disappoint. Stranded in the 60s, just days away from armageddon, the Umbrella Academy finds themselves as the only ones that can stop this world from ending. Can they stop bickering long enough to return things back to normal? Check out this recap & review to find out!

**Please** leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
